<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871002-0068 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:I.C.H. Corp.</HL><DD> 10/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> ICH SLHCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)FINANCIAL, INSURANCE, MUTUAL FUNDS, ACCOUNTING, LEASING (FIN)INSURANCE (INS) </IN><TEXT>   I.C.H. Corp. said it completed the sale of its Security Trust Life Insurance Co. unit to Nashville, Tenn.-based Southlife Holding Co. for $95 million cash and Security Trust's statutory net operating gains for the nine months ended Sept. 30.    In addition, two I.C.H. insurance subsidiaries purchased certain Southlife securities for $20 million. I.C.H., a Louisville, Ky.-based insurance holding company, also agreed to sell privately 140,000 shares of a new series of nonconvertible preferred stock to certain Southlife insurance subsidiaries for $7 million.    The preferred stock would pay a $4.50-a-share dividend annually, or 9% of the $50 stated value, and may be redeemed at any time at I.C.H.'s option without premium. </TEXT></DOC>